                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_kar" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kar</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>karæ</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>возраст</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>age</q></abv:tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>æmgar</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ровесник</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>person of the same age</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из %iæm-kar%i) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from %iæm-kar%i) </note></sense></re><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>mæ karæn qæd æmæ dūr dær nal ī<note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из слов Чендзе Абаевой, дожившей до 140 лет)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from the words of Chendze Abaeva, who lived to be 140 years old)</note></quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>моего возраста нет даже дерева и камня</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>There is even no wood or stone of my age</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>æz dær adtæn dæ kari</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>и я была в твоем возрасте</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>I was your age once</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>100</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Сближается с <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-k˳ra</w> <gloss><q>возраст</q></gloss></mentioned>. Дальнейшее не ясно. Не исключается иранское происхождение; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>kry’</w> <gloss><q>время</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/> <gloss><q>период</q></gloss></mentioned>. В этом случае абхазское слово может быть заимствованием из аланского.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>316</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>1120</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It is close to <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-k˳ra</w> <gloss><q>age</q></gloss></mentioned>. The rest is not clear. Iranian origin is not excluded; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>kry’</w> <gloss><q>time</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/> <gloss><q>period</q></gloss></mentioned>. In this case the Abkhaz word might be borrowed from Alan.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>316</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>1120</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>